x4freetext: The target thickness was approximately 200 ug/cm2,
determined via alpha particle energy loss measurement
active areas of 50 mm2 were used to measure the
The targets were mounted on a remotely controlled
target ladder in the center of the scattering
The energies of the alpha beam were 16.14 and 19.46
MeV with typical beam currents of 150-200 pnA.
An aperture of 2 x 6 mm was mounted on the target
ladder to check the beam position and size of the
beamspot before and after every change of the beam
The overall energy spread of the 1 mm collimated beam
after the analyzing magnet was around 100 keV which
is the dominating contribution of the energy
degree were measured at energies of Elab =16.14 and
19.46 MeV in 1 degree step between 20 and 100 deg.,
and in 2.5 deg. steps in the 100 - 175 deg. region.
